[{"id":"VR857492","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows 2 blocks labeled Material 1 and Material 2. The block labeled Material 1 is in the shape of a semicircle and is on top of the block labeled Material 2. The block labeled Material 2 is in the shape of a rectangle and a horizontal interface is shown where the blocks meet. A vertical dash line intersects the center of the interface at a right angle. A light ray originating from the left of the figure is shown entering through Material 1, traveling down and to the right. It reaches the interface at an angle relative to the vertical dash line labeled theta sub i is greater than 74 degrees. The light ray then reflects up and to the right. A note indicates the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857492.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two transparent blocks are in contact at an interface, as shown in the figure. The top block is in the shape of a semicircle and is made from material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> of refractive index <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub 1\"><math alttext=\"n sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>. The bottom block is rectangular and is made from material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> of refractive index <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub 2\"><math alttext=\"n sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>. A light ray is directed into the top block and is then incident on the interface between the two blocks. The critical angle at this interface is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"74 degrees\"><math alttext=\"74 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>74</mn><mo>°</mo></math></span></span>, in that an angle of incidence <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub i\"><math alttext=\"theta sub i\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></math></span></span> greater than this results in total internal reflection at the interface. If the bottom block is replaced with another rectangular block made from a different material of refractive index <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half n sub 2\"><math alttext=\"one half n sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, what is the critical angle in the new scenario?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR857492_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"8 degrees\"><math alttext=\"8 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>8</mn><mo>°</mo></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"16 degrees\"><math alttext=\"16 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>16</mn><mo>°</mo></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"29 degrees\"><math alttext=\"29 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>29</mn><mo>°</mo></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"37 degrees\"><math alttext=\"37 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>37</mn><mo>°</mo></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]